verses.text_plain: The word of the Lord also came unto me, saying,
verses.verse_html: 1The word of the Lord also came unto me, saying,

verses.text_plain: Son of man, thou dwellest in the midst of a rebellious house, which have eyes to see, and see not; they have ears to hear, and hear not: for they are a rebellious house.
verses.verse_html: 2Son of man, thou dwellest in the midst of a rebellious house, which have eyes to see, and see not; they have ears to hear, and hear not: for they are a rebellious house.

verses.text_plain: Therefore, thou son of man, prepare thee stuff for removing, and remove by day in their sight; and thou shalt remove from thy place to another place in their sight: it may be they will consider, though they be a rebellious house.
verses.verse_html:
3Therefore, thou son of man, prepare thee stuff for removing, and remove by day in their sight; and thou shalt remove from thy place to another place in their sight: it may be they will consider, though they be a rebellious house. ▼
▼ stuff: or, instruments

tokens.text: it may be they will consider

verses.text_plain: Then shalt thou bring forth thy stuff by day in their sight, as stuff for removing: and thou shalt go forth at even in their sight, as they that go forth into captivity.
verses.verse_html:
4Then shalt thou bring forth thy stuff by day in their sight, as stuff for removing: and thou shalt go forth at even in their sight, as they that go forth into captivity. ▼
▼ as they…: Heb. as the goings forth of captivity

footnotes.body_text: ▼ as they…: Heb. as the goings forth of captivity
footnotes.body_html: ▼ as they…: Heb. as the goings forth of captivity

verses.text_plain: Dig thou through the wall in their sight, and carry out thereby.
verses.verse_html:
5Dig thou through the wall in their sight, and carry out thereby. ▼
▼ Dig…: Heb. Dig for thee

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Dig…: Heb. Dig for thee

verses.text_plain: In their sight shalt thou bear it upon thy shoulders, and carry it forth in the twilight: thou shalt cover thy face, that thou see not the ground: for I have set thee for a sign unto the house of Israel.
verses.verse_html: 6In their sight shalt thou bear it upon thy shoulders, and carry it forth in the twilight: thou shalt cover thy face, that thou see not the ground: for I have set thee for a sign unto the house of Israel.

verses.text_plain: And I did so as I was commanded: I brought forth my stuff by day, as stuff for captivity, and in the even I digged through the wall with mine hand; I brought it forth in the twilight, and I bare it upon my shoulder in their sight.
verses.verse_html:
7And I did so as I was commanded: I brought forth my stuff by day, as stuff for captivity, and in the even I digged through the wall with mine hand; I brought it forth in the twilight, and I bare it upon my shoulder in their sight. ▼
▼ digged: Heb. digged for me

footnotes.body_html: ▼ digged: Heb. digged for me

verses.text_plain: And in the morning came the word of the Lord unto me, saying,
verses.verse_html: 8And in the morning came the word of the Lord unto me, saying,

verses.text_plain: Son of man, hath not the house of Israel, the rebellious house, said unto thee, What doest thou?
verses.verse_html: 9Son of man, hath not the house of Israel, the rebellious house, said unto thee, What doest thou?

verses.text_plain: Say thou unto them, Thus saith the Lord God; This burden concerneth the prince in Jerusalem, and all the house of Israel that are among them.
verses.verse_html: 10Say thou unto them, Thus saith the Lord God; This burden concerneth the prince in Jerusalem, and all the house of Israel that are among them.

verses.text_plain: Say, I am your sign: like as I have done, so shall it be done unto them: they shall remove and go into captivity.
verses.verse_html:
11Say, I am your sign: like as I have done, so shall it be done unto them: they shall remove and go into captivity. ▼
▼ they…: Heb. by removing go into captivity

footnotes.body_text: ▼ they…: Heb. by removing go into captivity
footnotes.body_html: ▼ they…: Heb. by removing go into captivity

verses.text_plain: And the prince that is among them shall bear upon his shoulder in the twilight, and shall go forth: they shall dig through the wall to carry out thereby: he shall cover his face, that he see not the ground with his eyes.
verses.verse_html: 12And the prince that is among them shall bear upon his shoulder in the twilight, and shall go forth: they shall dig through the wall to carry out thereby: he shall cover his face, that he see not the ground with his eyes.

verses.text_plain: My net also will I spread upon him, and he shall be taken in my snare: and I will bring him to Babylon to the land of the Chaldeans; yet shall he not see it, though he shall die there.
verses.verse_html: 13My net also will I spread upon him, and he shall be taken in my snare: and I will bring him to Babylon to the land of the Chaldeans; yet shall he not see it, though he shall die there.

tokens.text: upon him, and he shall be taken

verses.text_plain: And I will scatter toward every wind all that are about him to help him, and all his bands; and I will draw out the sword after them.
verses.verse_html: 14And I will scatter toward every wind all that are about him to help him, and all his bands; and I will draw out the sword after them.

verses.text_plain: And they shall know that I am the Lord, when I shall scatter them among the nations, and disperse them in the countries.
verses.verse_html: 15And they shall know that I am the Lord, when I shall scatter them among the nations, and disperse them in the countries.

verses.text_plain: But I will leave a few men of them from the sword, from the famine, and from the pestilence; that they may declare all their abominations among the heathen whither they come; and they shall know that I am the Lord.
verses.verse_html:
16But I will leave a few men of them from the sword, from the famine, and from the pestilence; that they may declare all their abominations among the heathen whither they come; and they shall know that I am the Lord. ▼
▼ a few…: Heb. men of number

footnotes.body_text: ▼ a few…: Heb. men of number
footnotes.body_html: ▼ a few…: Heb. men of number

verses.text_plain: Moreover the word of the Lord came to me, saying,
verses.verse_html: 17Moreover the word of the Lord came to me, saying,

verses.text_plain: Son of man, eat thy bread with quaking, and drink thy water with trembling and with carefulness;
verses.verse_html: 18Son of man, eat thy bread with quaking, and drink thy water with trembling and with carefulness;

verses.text_plain: And say unto the people of the land, Thus saith the Lord God of the inhabitants of Jerusalem, and of the land of Israel; They shall eat their bread with carefulness, and drink their water with astonishment, that her land may be desolate from all that is therein, because of the violence of all them that dwell therein.
verses.verse_html:
19And say unto the people of the land, Thus saith the Lord God of the inhabitants of Jerusalem, and of the land of Israel; They shall eat their bread with carefulness, and drink their water with astonishment, that her land may be desolate from all that is therein, because of the violence of all them that dwell therein. ▼
▼ all that…: Heb. the fulness thereof

footnotes.body_text: ▼ all that…: Heb. the fulness thereof
footnotes.body_html: ▼ all that…: Heb. the fulness thereof

verses.text_plain: And the cities that are inhabited shall be laid waste, and the land shall be desolate; and ye shall know that I am the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 20And the cities that are inhabited shall be laid waste, and the land shall be desolate; and ye shall know that I am the Lord.

verses.text_plain: And the word of the Lord came unto me, saying,
verses.verse_html: 21And the word of the Lord came unto me, saying,

verses.text_plain: Son of man, what is that proverb that ye have in the land of Israel, saying, The days are prolonged, and every vision faileth?
verses.verse_html: 22Son of man, what is that proverb that ye have in the land of Israel, saying, The days are prolonged, and every vision faileth?

verses.text_plain: Tell them therefore, Thus saith the Lord God; I will make this proverb to cease, and they shall no more use it as a proverb in Israel; but say unto them, The days are at hand, and the effect of every vision.
verses.verse_html: 23Tell them therefore, Thus saith the Lord God; I will make this proverb to cease, and they shall no more use it as a proverb in Israel; but say unto them, The days are at hand, and the effect of every vision.

tokens.text: and they shall no more use it as a proverb

verses.text_plain: For there shall be no more any vain vision nor flattering divination within the house of Israel.
verses.verse_html: 24For there shall be no more any vain vision nor flattering divination within the house of Israel.

tokens.text: For there shall be no more any vain

verses.text_plain: For I am the Lord: I will speak, and the word that I shall speak shall come to pass; it shall be no more prolonged: for in your days, O rebellious house, will I say the word, and will perform it, saith the Lord God.
verses.verse_html: 25For I am the Lord: I will speak, and the word that I shall speak shall come to pass; it shall be no more prolonged: for in your days, O rebellious house, will I say the word, and will perform it, saith the Lord God.

tokens.text: it shall be no more prolonged

verses.text_plain: Again the word of the Lord came to me, saying,
verses.verse_html: 26Again the word of the Lord came to me, saying,

verses.text_plain: Son of man, behold, they of the house of Israel say, The vision that he seeth is for many days to come, and he prophesieth of the times that are far off.
verses.verse_html: 27Son of man, behold, they of the house of Israel say, The vision that he seeth is for many days to come, and he prophesieth of the times that are far off.

verses.text_plain: Therefore say unto them, Thus saith the Lord God; There shall none of my words be prolonged any more, but the word which I have spoken shall be done, saith the Lord God.
verses.verse_html: 28Therefore say unto them, Thus saith the Lord God; There shall none of my words be prolonged any more, but the word which I have spoken shall be done, saith the Lord God.

tokens.text: There shall none of my words
